w:r.w:t: Happy holidays from our family to yours!

Holiday newsletters are a great way to keep the people closest to you updated on your family's life. It's also a fun way to share holiday greetings or write about your past year's experiences. To start, let each of your family write down their own articles in the newsletter. Add photographs from family vacations. Think about what you would tell your family and friends if you could see them.

A family newsletter is also a fun activity to do as a family. Everyone feels included when you share memories with each other. Sit down and talk about the important things that happened in the past year. Also, think about who's reading your newsletter. What would your friends or distant relatives most want to hear about? Write down your ideas and then organize your list into categories.
